# Scaffolded by create-harness-app. Materialized as `.gitignore` in the target
# project (source filename is `gitignore` with no leading dot, because `npm
# pack` renames any top-level `.gitignore` in a package to `.npmignore`).
# The scaffold manifest maps `gitignore` -> `.gitignore` at scaffold time.
#
# Captured as E-12 in experiments/2026-05-17--e11-e12-ignore-configs/.

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# Logs / env / secrets
*.log
.env
.env.local

# Dependency-audit staging dir (ADR-0023-dependency-audit.md).
# scripts/dep-audit.ts writes resolved requirements files here before
# piping them to pip-audit; the dir is rm -rf'd on completion, but a
# crashed run could leave it behind.
.dep-audit/

# Profiling perf budgets are per-fork policy: local experiments keep them
# untracked; consumers that want CI-binding budgets delete this line and
# commit harness/profiling/budgets.toml (template: budgets.example.toml).
harness/profiling/budgets.toml

# Harness internals
# Top-level consumer-side .harness/ is local-only (per-fork policy / scratch).
# The slot-side governance file at harness/.harness/governance.toml is the
# *committed* eat-own-dogfood seed — un-ignore it explicitly below.
.harness/
!harness/.harness/
!harness/.harness/**
.worktrees/
.sentrux/
.apss/
# APSS code-topology producer output — regenerated on every sensors-gate
# cycle (closed loop). Committing the snapshot would make the repo a
# moving target on every run.
.topology/

# Agent-plugin vendor symlinks are now COMMITTED so they exist the instant
# the repo is cloned (per WS1 fork-readiness spec, dogfood F-001). The
# canonical body lives at AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md / GEMINI.md / .codex /
# .gemini are committed symlinks pointing at it. `just bootstrap` verifies
# and repairs the symlinks idempotently. Do not re-add ignore entries here.

# Node / TS
node_modules/
pnpm-lock.yaml
dist/
build/
coverage/
.nyc_output/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Rust
Cargo.lock
target/
**/target/
*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak

# Python
uv.lock
.venv/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
*.egg-info/

# Go
go.sum
.claude/settings.local.json
